00:58:37,514 --> 00:58:39,348
Let me tell you something.

737
00:58:39,850 --> 00:58:41,308
I can't ski!

738
00:59:13,884 --> 00:59:16,051
Once Gus contacts
the Vulcan satellite...

739
00:59:16,219 --> 00:59:18,220
he orders it to search
through space...

740
00:59:18,388 --> 00:59:21,182
around where Krypton
went bye-bye.

741
00:59:30,650 --> 00:59:34,236
Then the laser probe locks
on to a floating chunk of Kryptonite.

742
00:59:34,404 --> 00:59:36,489
The computer analyzes
the components...

743
00:59:36,698 --> 00:59:39,992
and the boys at the lab
duplicate the stuff down here.

744
00:59:40,577 --> 00:59:42,411
"Unknown"?

745
00:59:42,871 --> 00:59:44,413
"Unknown"?

746
01:00:01,640 --> 01:00:03,766
What the hell,
he ain't gonna smoke it.

747
01:00:09,773 --> 01:00:12,274
Mr. White can't be responsible.

748
01:00:14,528 --> 01:00:15,736
Where is he?

749
01:00:15,946 --> 01:00:17,530
Please, Mr. Stokis.

750
01:00:17,948 --> 01:00:19,657
He'll pay for this.

751
01:00:21,159 --> 01:00:22,701
Get out your wallet!

752
01:00:23,703 --> 01:00:26,956
- Good morning.
- Don't you "good morning" me.

753
01:00:28,416 --> 01:00:32,628
"Old, old relationships
suddenly seem very much the same.

754
01:00:32,796 --> 01:00:34,463
The prettiest girl in the school..."

755
01:00:36,299 --> 01:00:38,592
is still the prettiest girl
in the school.

756
01:00:43,181 --> 01:00:46,433
- Hello?
- Hello. Oh, hi, Clark.

757
01:00:46,643 --> 01:00:51,188
Lana! Hi, I was just
thinking about you.

758
01:00:51,398 --> 01:00:52,731
Oh, um...

759
01:00:52,941 --> 01:00:55,109
Listen, I have a problem with Ricky.

760
01:00:55,277 --> 01:00:56,610
Why? What happened to Ricky?

761
01:00:56,778 --> 01:01:00,322
It's Superman's autograph you got him.
He got carried away...

762
01:01:00,490 --> 01:01:03,492
and told the kids Superman
was coming on his birthday.

763
01:01:03,743 --> 01:01:04,994
Okay, it was wrong...

764
01:01:05,161 --> 01:01:08,831
but when Wednesday comes and
Superman doesn't show, it's gonna...

765
01:01:09,833 --> 01:01:13,460
Well, Lana, in this case I think
I can go ahead and speak for Superman.

766
01:01:13,628 --> 01:01:15,713
I mean, he and I
are pretty close, you know.

767
01:01:15,922 --> 01:01:19,967
And you can tell Ricky that Superman
will be there on Wednesday, all right?

768
01:01:21,720 --> 01:01:25,139
Well, he's gonna get the best
home-cooked meal he's had...

769
01:01:25,515 --> 01:01:26,682
in a long time.

770
01:01:26,850 --> 01:01:29,852
- Tell Superman we think he's wonderful.
- All right.

771
01:01:30,020 --> 01:01:32,146
- But, Clark...
- Yeah?

772
01:01:32,522 --> 01:01:33,856
You're the best.

773
01:01:38,361 --> 01:01:41,322
And I'll take it to
the Supreme Court if I have to.

774
01:01:41,531 --> 01:01:44,825
But it wasn't our fault.
It was an act of God.

775
01:01:45,035 --> 01:01:46,827
In a church?

776
01:01:59,466 --> 01:02:00,549
Hey!

777
01:02:00,759 --> 01:02:02,718
Here's that compound you ordered.

778
01:02:02,886 --> 01:02:04,803
Can't imagine what you want with it.

779
01:02:04,971 --> 01:02:06,347
But you got it.

780
01:02:12,646 --> 01:02:15,564
What the hell am I afraid for?
I'm from Earth.

781
01:02:21,279 --> 01:02:23,405
Lana, I really wasn't expecting all this.

782
01:02:23,657 --> 01:02:26,200
I guess they did get
a little carried away.

783
01:02:40,048 --> 01:02:43,300
Superman, we all know...

784
01:02:43,927 --> 01:02:46,679
that you're not looking
for honors and awards.

785
01:02:47,514 --> 01:02:51,100
But when we heard that you were
coming to see your pal Ricky...

786
01:02:51,309 --> 01:02:55,104
we realized that this was
our chance to say thank you.

787
01:02:55,313 --> 01:02:57,690
First, for putting out
the Lake Comooga fire.

788
01:02:58,191 --> 01:03:01,443
And not least,
for saving little Ricky.

789
01:03:01,945 --> 01:03:04,613
So since you already have
the key to our hearts...

790
01:03:04,781 --> 01:03:06,949
Superman...

791
01:03:07,117 --> 01:03:11,203
may I present you
with the key to the city.

792
01:03:11,413 --> 01:03:12,788
Thank you, sir.

793
01:03:16,835 --> 01:03:18,043
Thank you.

794
01:03:34,477 --> 01:03:36,145
As you were.

795
01:03:39,149 --> 01:03:40,482
Now listen up.

796
01:03:40,984 --> 01:03:42,818
I just came in directly...

797
01:03:42,986 --> 01:03:45,154
from the Pentagon...

798
01:03:45,405 --> 01:03:49,491
and you better believe there's
a damn good reason that I did.

799
01:03:50,493 --> 01:03:52,828
Because God has given us...

800
01:03:52,996 --> 01:03:56,498
one of the greatest gifts in the world...

801
01:03:56,875 --> 01:03:58,625
Chemicals.

802
01:03:59,627 --> 01:04:04,256
Now, you people, you like to go sit
in church on Sunday, don't you?

803
01:04:04,632 --> 01:04:07,092
You like to sit and watch
the Super Bowl.

804
01:04:07,260 --> 01:04:08,343
Yeah.

805
01:04:08,511 --> 01:04:10,596
Sit on what?!

806
01:04:11,973 --> 01:04:16,185
You sit on molded, plastic seats!

807
01:04:16,978 --> 01:04:20,522
Molded to your well-fed behinds.

808
01:04:22,025 --> 01:04:26,361
Now, I don't have to tell you
that America leads the world...

809
01:04:26,529 --> 01:04:27,905
in high-grade plastics.

810
01:04:28,364 --> 01:04:32,701
We cannot afford
a chemical-plastics gap.

811
01:04:33,953 --> 01:04:35,162
Now, listen to me.

812
01:04:35,914 --> 01:04:37,539
Do you want...

813
01:04:37,707 --> 01:04:42,127
our president of the United States
sitting down...

814
01:04:42,921 --> 01:04:44,880
to write a peace treaty...

815
01:04:45,048 --> 01:04:47,966
and have his ballpoint pen bust open...

816
01:04:48,176 --> 01:04:51,386
and the ink run out all over
his nice, clean pants...

817
01:04:51,554 --> 01:04:53,388
in front of the world leaders?

818
01:04:53,556 --> 01:04:55,432
No. No.

819
01:04:55,934 --> 01:04:57,726
Now, we all know...

820
01:04:57,936 --> 01:05:02,231
that last week, half of
this great nation of ours...

821
01:05:02,482 --> 01:05:04,066
almost bit the bullet...

822
01:05:04,734 --> 01:05:07,194
if it wasn't for this man here.

823
01:05:09,364 --> 01:05:13,742
And all I can say is,
thank the Lord for Superman.

824
01:05:19,707 --> 01:05:21,834
Superman, you saved our bacon...

825
01:05:22,043 --> 01:05:24,336
and I'd like to show our gratitude.

826
01:05:27,465 --> 01:05:31,844
This is a small token
of our appreciation...

827
01:05:32,053 --> 01:05:36,682
to show to you for saving us
from a chemical-plant disaster.

828
01:05:42,939 --> 01:05:44,606
Thank you very much, general.

829
01:05:45,108 --> 01:05:47,276
This is very nice. Thank you.

830
01:05:58,705 --> 01:05:59,746
It's very nice.

831
01:06:07,130 --> 01:06:10,799
Unknown. How am I supposed
to know what "unknown" means?

832
01:06:11,050 --> 01:06:14,094
It means unknown. It means
nobody knows what it means.

833
01:06:14,262 --> 01:06:16,471
- Hello, boss?
- Gus?

834
01:06:16,973 --> 01:06:19,808
- Gus Gorman here.
- I know that. How did it go?

835
01:06:20,518 --> 01:06:24,104
You know how they're always
trying to find the secret recipe...

836
01:06:24,314 --> 01:06:26,106
in that chicken in the bucket?

837
01:06:26,316 --> 01:06:28,317
And nobody seems to know
the ingredient...

838
01:06:28,526 --> 01:06:30,652
because it's unknown, right?

839
01:06:31,321 --> 01:06:35,657
In the Kryptonite there was an unknown
element and Superman didn't die.

840
01:06:36,534 --> 01:06:38,660
He didn't die.

841
01:06:39,329 --> 01:06:41,997
I ask you to kill Superman...

842
01:06:42,165 --> 01:06:46,335
and you're telling me you couldn't
even do that one simple thing.

843
01:06:50,673 --> 01:06:51,798
Hello?

844
01:07:05,688 --> 01:07:08,273
He hasn't had
an afternoon nap for years.

845
01:07:08,483 --> 01:07:12,152
This is the biggest day of his life.
I don't know how to thank you.

846
01:07:12,320 --> 01:07:13,987
You did with that wonderful lunch.

847
01:07:14,155 --> 01:07:17,366
Oh, well, I do like to cook.

848
01:07:18,368 --> 01:07:20,369
- You'll take some coffee?
- Yes, please.

849
01:07:20,578 --> 01:07:22,704
- Decaffeinated, of course.
- Right.

850
01:07:27,710 --> 01:07:30,212
Hello? Yes.

851
01:07:31,881 --> 01:07:33,215
What?

852
01:07:33,591 --> 01:07:35,467
Oh, really?

853
01:07:35,677 --> 01:07:36,885
Yeah, he's here.

854
01:07:37,053 --> 01:07:39,054
I'll tell him.
Okay, thanks. Bye-bye.

855
01:07:39,222 --> 01:07:42,182
Superman, that was my friend Betty.

856
01:07:42,392 --> 01:07:45,894
There's an accident on the bridge.
A trailer crashed through the rail.

857
01:07:46,062 --> 01:07:49,147
It's hanging off the bridge
and the driver's in the cab.

858
01:07:49,691 --> 01:07:52,109
I'm sorry.
I hate to make you rush off.

859
01:07:52,735 --> 01:07:54,069
Well, there's no rush.

860
01:07:54,737 --> 01:07:58,490
- But the bridge...
- It's okay. I always get there on time.

861
01:07:58,700 --> 01:08:00,367
Come on, let's relax a little.

862
01:08:14,215 --> 01:08:17,718
It's unusual finding a good-looking girl
like you alone like this.

863
01:08:28,354 --> 01:08:33,275
Listen, are you sure you shouldn't
do something about the bridge?

864
01:08:33,943 --> 01:08:35,110
What bridge?

865
01:08:40,450 --> 01:08:41,575
You're right.

866
01:08:45,788 --> 01:08:47,539
I have to get going.

867
01:08:56,466 --> 01:08:58,091
Get him out of there. Come on.

868
01:08:58,301 --> 01:08:59,926
Get him out! Get him out quick!

869
01:09:00,136 --> 01:09:02,804
Come on. Get him away.
That thing's gonna go.

870
01:09:17,695 --> 01:09:19,738
Everybody okay? Joe?

871
01:09:20,490 --> 01:09:21,740
What can I do to help?

872
01:09:21,949 --> 01:09:23,450
Not much of anything now.

873
01:09:23,659 --> 01:09:26,203
If only you'd got here
a minute sooner.

874
01:10:41,571 --> 01:10:44,114
"At a special session
of the General Assembly...

875
01:10:44,282 --> 01:10:47,534
178 countries voted
to censure Superman...

876
01:10:47,702 --> 01:10:50,162
with only Colombia abstaining".

877
01:10:50,329 --> 01:10:51,830
I can tell you one thing.

878
01:10:52,039 --> 01:10:55,876
He wasn't so mean and nasty
the other day in Smallville.

879
01:10:56,085 --> 01:10:58,503
In fact, he was so full of niceness...

880
01:10:58,671 --> 01:11:01,047
I hated laying that big chunk of...

881
01:11:02,758 --> 01:11:04,759
Kryptonite. Don't you see?

882
01:11:04,927 --> 01:11:08,263
That stuff we ran off in the lab
wasn't a complete failure after all.

883
01:11:08,431 --> 01:11:11,308
Right after Gus gave it to him,
he started to turn into...

884
01:11:11,517 --> 01:11:13,602
an ornery, evil, malicious, selfish...

885
01:11:13,811 --> 01:11:15,729
- A normal person.
- Yes.

886
01:11:16,314 --> 01:11:19,858
And now that Superman
is out of the nice-guy business...

887
01:11:20,026 --> 01:11:21,735
We can get to work on that oil.

888
01:11:45,468 --> 01:11:49,638
And now, the supreme
moment, as the last runner...

889
01:11:49,805 --> 01:11:53,767
the one given the great honor
of lighting the ceremonial flame...

890
01:11:53,935 --> 01:11:58,063
runs the last leg of a marathon
that began seven days ago...

891
01:11:58,272 --> 01:12:02,984
as this torch has been passed
from athlete to athlete...

892
01:12:03,194 --> 01:12:05,946
for 970 miles...

893
01:12:06,113 --> 01:12:07,948
across the country.

894
01:12:49,115 --> 01:12:52,409
How can he say that pure categories
have no objective meaning...

895
01:12:52,618 --> 01:12:55,453
in transcendental logic?
What about synthetic unity?

896
01:12:58,332 --> 01:13:00,083
Hi, honey! Am I in your way?

897
01:13:00,251 --> 01:13:03,211
- Stick around, you may learn something.
- Hi, Lorelei.

898
01:13:03,379 --> 01:13:07,048
All the oil tankers in the world
are totally controlled by computers.

899
01:13:07,216 --> 01:13:10,093
They tell them where to go,
how much oil to pick up...

900
01:13:10,303 --> 01:13:12,012
and where to deliver it.

901
01:13:12,179 --> 01:13:14,055
Don't they have captains
on these ships?

902
01:13:14,223 --> 01:13:15,682
Yes, but they don't need them.

903
01:13:15,850 --> 01:13:19,144
That's a throwback to some
sentimental, seafaring baloney.

904
01:13:19,312 --> 01:13:23,023
You will command the tankers
to sail toward a 50-mile area...

905
01:13:23,190 --> 01:13:25,066
in the middle of the Atlantic Ocean.

906
01:13:25,234 --> 01:13:26,901
And do what?

907
01:13:27,069 --> 01:13:29,279
And do nothing.

908
01:13:29,488 --> 01:13:31,740
Just sit there.

909
01:13:32,908 --> 01:13:35,785
How are all the people
gonna get their oil?

910
01:13:36,954 --> 01:13:39,372
You catch on fast, old buddy.

911
01:13:42,084 --> 01:13:45,253
Every oil pump in America is run by...

912
01:13:45,463 --> 01:13:48,214
- Computers. I know.
- Will you stop interrupting?!

913
01:13:48,424 --> 01:13:49,591
I'm sorry.

914
01:13:49,925 --> 01:13:53,720
You will command the pumps
to stop pumping.

915
01:13:53,888 --> 01:13:57,807
Then I want you to program
one special command...

916
01:13:58,017 --> 01:14:00,101
into all these systems.

917
01:14:00,269 --> 01:14:03,063
Tell them these orders
are irreversible.

918
01:14:03,272 --> 01:14:07,025
So it would be impossible
for anybody to switch them back.

919
01:14:07,234 --> 01:14:09,110
Can you do this for me, old buddy?

920
01:14:09,653 --> 01:14:11,529
Old pal?

921
01:14:18,871 --> 01:14:21,289
You know, you get your way
all the time.

922
01:14:22,458 --> 01:14:24,250
And it's not right.

923
01:14:26,670 --> 01:14:28,797
I wanna know when I get a taste.

924
01:14:35,262 --> 01:14:39,516
I think you've already had
a taste of freedom, haven't you?

925
01:14:39,725 --> 01:14:42,268
Or would you prefer jail?

926
01:14:42,478 --> 01:14:44,312
You can't run that jail number on me.

927
01:14:44,647 --> 01:14:48,233
Because I know I mean more to you
out here doing things for you...

928
01:14:48,442 --> 01:14:51,152
than sitting in jail
doing nothing for nobody.

929
01:14:52,905 --> 01:14:53,988
I see.

930
01:14:54,156 --> 01:14:55,990
What do you want?

931
01:15:02,331 --> 01:15:04,791
What? A wastebasket?

932
01:15:05,000 --> 01:15:07,127
No. These are plans.

933
01:15:08,003 --> 01:15:09,504
Blueprints.

934
01:15:10,047 --> 01:15:12,132
- For what?
- A computer.

935
01:15:12,299 --> 01:15:15,135
- We've already got computers.
- No, not like this.

936
01:15:15,302 --> 01:15:18,847
There's not a computer like this
in the whole world anyplace.

937
01:15:19,390 --> 01:15:21,266
It doesn't exist. You see...

938
01:15:21,559 --> 01:15:22,851
we have to build it.

939
01:15:23,394 --> 01:15:24,477
What will it do?

940
01:15:24,812 --> 01:15:26,646
Anything I tell it.

941
01:15:27,189 --> 01:15:29,357
What will it do for me?

942
01:15:29,525 --> 01:15:33,820
For you? It will do anything you
tell me to tell it to do for you.

943
01:15:34,071 --> 01:15:35,405
Wow.

944
01:15:40,202 --> 01:15:41,786
Tell me.

945
01:15:43,706 --> 01:15:47,000
First of all, if anyone attacks
this machine or anything...

946
01:15:47,209 --> 01:15:49,085
the computer counterattacks it.

947
01:15:49,295 --> 01:15:52,297
I mean, it finds their weaknesses
and wipes them out.

948
01:15:52,798 --> 01:15:53,882
Right, old buddy.

949
01:15:54,091 --> 01:15:57,886
You deal with my oil
and I'll build you your machine.

950
01:16:01,557 --> 01:16:03,224
Okay, I'll do it.

951
01:16:03,392 --> 01:16:06,936
But I'm not so sure about
this irreversible business.

952
01:16:24,079 --> 01:16:26,748
They all kind of went...
What the hell?

953
01:16:30,169 --> 01:16:32,629
That's it. The last tanker.

954
01:16:33,339 --> 01:16:36,257
They're all mine now. All mine.

955
01:16:36,800 --> 01:16:38,301
Yay.

956
01:16:38,511 --> 01:16:40,762
Not quite.

957
01:16:40,930 --> 01:16:43,431
What's that in
the upper-middle quadrant?

958
01:16:44,433 --> 01:16:45,934
It's a tanker.

959
01:16:48,062 --> 01:16:49,979
And it's going the wrong way.

960
01:17:00,783 --> 01:17:01,950
Skipper?

961
01:17:02,117 --> 01:17:04,786
There it is again.
"Proceed immediately to...

962
01:17:04,995 --> 01:17:08,081
latitude 30 north, longitude 45 west.

963
01:17:09,792 --> 01:17:11,459
There await further orders".

964
01:17:11,627 --> 01:17:13,795
Hell, that's the middle of the Atlantic.

965
01:17:13,963 --> 01:17:16,881
I'm not taking my ship there
just to await further orders...

966
01:17:17,091 --> 01:17:18,633
no matter what that says.

967
01:17:18,842 --> 01:17:22,470
We're supposed to go to Metropolis,
and we're going to Metropolis.

968
01:17:22,638 --> 01:17:23,930
All right.

969
01:17:36,318 --> 01:17:37,652
That's where she is. Yeah.

970
01:17:37,820 --> 01:17:39,904
Come on, get it up there.

971
01:17:41,323 --> 01:17:42,699
Miss?

972
01:17:43,242 --> 01:17:45,493
Miss, can you hear me?

973
01:17:45,661 --> 01:17:48,329
Listen, we are here to help you.

974
01:17:48,539 --> 01:17:52,000
Don't jump. I repeat, do not jump!

975
01:17:53,627 --> 01:17:55,003
Thought you'd never get here.

976
01:17:55,879 --> 01:17:58,631
Don't expect me to save you.
I don't do that anymore.

977
01:17:58,841 --> 01:17:59,924
Don't worry.

978
01:18:00,092 --> 01:18:02,844
I'm long past saving.

979
01:18:07,725 --> 01:18:09,183
Well...

980
01:18:09,852 --> 01:18:11,686
don't let me keep you
from anything.

981
01:18:12,354 --> 01:18:13,938
I'm not in a rush.

982
01:18:19,778 --> 01:18:21,738
What did you have in mind?

983
01:18:22,114 --> 01:18:23,698
Lots of things.

984
01:18:23,866 --> 01:18:25,158
Oh, yeah?

985
01:18:26,660 --> 01:18:27,994
Ooo...

986
01:18:28,245 --> 01:18:31,164
If you'll just do me
one little favor first.

987
01:18:31,373 --> 01:18:32,707
What's that?

988
01:18:33,208 --> 01:18:34,959
Well...

989
01:18:35,502 --> 01:18:37,712
See, there's this little boat...

990
01:18:37,921 --> 01:18:41,633
and it's not going where
it's supposed to go and...

991
01:19:18,253 --> 01:19:19,921
Stop all engines!

992
01:19:20,923 --> 01:19:22,590
Stop all engines!

993
01:20:15,978 --> 01:20:17,478
Hi.

994
01:20:33,036 --> 01:20:35,455
How about a little après-ski?

995
01:20:46,425 --> 01:20:47,842
Champagne?

996
01:21:11,617 --> 01:21:13,451
Take your turn like everybody else!

997
01:21:13,660 --> 01:21:15,703
Stop it!

998
01:21:18,457 --> 01:21:20,500
He's coming over here, Martha.

999
01:21:24,046 --> 01:21:25,463
Don't you do that!

1000
01:21:27,049 --> 01:21:29,133
Don't! Please!

1001
01:21:35,349 --> 01:21:37,308
Hit him with your handbag!

1002
01:21:40,896 --> 01:21:44,232
Help me! Please, help me.
Somebody's beating up my husband.

1003
01:21:44,399 --> 01:21:48,027
- I've gotta call the police.
- Jack, go with her, okay?

1004
01:21:49,071 --> 01:21:51,572
The third one today,
and at night it's worse.

1005
01:21:51,782 --> 01:21:53,574
Somebody's behind this.

1006
01:21:53,784 --> 01:21:55,535
You can't tell me there's no oil.

1007
01:21:55,702 --> 01:21:58,079
You can't say someone's
not getting rich off this.

1008
01:21:58,288 --> 01:22:00,122
Someone's always getting rich.

1009
01:22:00,332 --> 01:22:02,333
You know who suffers? The small guy.

1010
01:22:02,543 --> 01:22:05,753
The East Coast gets
the brunt of the spill.

1011
01:22:48,463 --> 01:22:51,007
No, I cannot go out with you tonight.

1012
01:22:51,466 --> 01:22:53,009
No. I'm busy tomorrow night too.

1013
01:22:53,176 --> 01:22:54,969
Oh, yeah? Doing what?

1014
01:22:55,387 --> 01:22:57,221
I'll think of something. Look...

1015
01:22:57,431 --> 01:23:00,600
- I gotta go. Ricky needs me.
- Lana.

1016
01:23:00,767 --> 01:23:03,895
Brad, please stop calling me.
I've told you!

1017
01:23:04,062 --> 01:23:06,147
Well, you listen to me, huh?

1018
01:23:06,315 --> 01:23:08,316
You better start appreciating old Brad.

1019
01:23:08,734 --> 01:23:10,276
What else you got in Smallville?

1020
01:23:16,199 --> 01:23:18,743
What else have I got in Smallville?

1021
01:23:20,287 --> 01:23:22,288
I think I got the right answer.

1022
01:23:22,956 --> 01:23:24,332
So do I.

1023
01:23:33,425 --> 01:23:37,136
Smallville Airport, what flights
do you have to Metropolis tomorrow?

1024
01:23:42,768 --> 01:23:45,311
- Where do I put this?
- Over there.

1025
01:23:47,022 --> 01:23:50,066
- Where do you want this?
- Put it up there.

1026
01:23:53,362 --> 01:23:56,197
Are you kidding? I'm not going in there.

1027
01:24:17,219 --> 01:24:19,553
Hey, hey. Come on.

1028
01:24:28,063 --> 01:24:29,230
Just leave him alone.

1029
01:24:51,003 --> 01:24:53,129
I can't get through.
Something's happening.

1030
01:24:53,338 --> 01:24:55,131
Hey, look! Superman's drunk!

1031
01:24:55,340 --> 01:24:58,426
- I wanna see what's happening here.
- Ricky. Ricky!

1032
01:24:59,011 --> 01:25:01,929
- Ricky.
- Yeah, that's right.

1033
01:25:02,472 --> 01:25:04,765
- Thank you.
- It's a disgrace, that's what it is.

1034
01:25:04,933 --> 01:25:07,768
I'll tell you, nobody's ever
gonna trust that creep again.

1035
01:25:07,936 --> 01:25:09,395
He's washed up.

1036
01:25:12,899 --> 01:25:15,609
What are you looking at? Huh?

1037
01:25:15,986 --> 01:25:19,196
Excuse me. Superman? It's me, Ricky.

1038
01:25:19,406 --> 01:25:21,073
Ricky from Smallville.

1039
01:25:21,283 --> 01:25:23,034
Tell them you won't hurt anybody!

1040
01:25:23,243 --> 01:25:24,410
He's changed.

1041
01:25:24,578 --> 01:25:27,246
No! Maybe he's just sick.

1042
01:25:27,456 --> 01:25:29,290
Superman, please get better!

1043
01:25:29,499 --> 01:25:30,958
He's not listening to you.

1044
01:25:31,126 --> 01:25:34,962
Yes, he is. He can hear me.
He's got super-hearing.

1045
01:25:35,130 --> 01:25:37,757
Superman, you're just in a slump!

1046
01:25:37,924 --> 01:25:39,675
You'll be great again!

1047
01:25:39,885 --> 01:25:41,385
You can do it, Superman!

1048
01:25:41,595 --> 01:25:44,555
Superman, you can hear me, can't you?

1049
01:25:44,765 --> 01:25:47,308
Superman, you're just in a slump.

1050
01:25:47,476 --> 01:25:51,103
You'll be great again.
You can do it, superman.

1051
01:25:51,271 --> 01:25:54,315
Superman, you can hear me, can't you?

1052
01:26:14,503 --> 01:26:15,544
He's gone nuts!

1053
01:26:17,422 --> 01:26:18,464
Come on!

1054
01:27:45,427 --> 01:27:47,386
I can give as good as I get.

1055
01:27:48,513 --> 01:27:51,515
Oh, yeah? All right, come on! Come on!

1056
01:27:51,683 --> 01:27:53,434
Come on! Come on!

1057
01:28:18,919 --> 01:28:21,545
What's the matter, Kent?
Too warm for you, huh?

1058
01:28:23,673 --> 01:28:26,467
Come on, chicken! Come and get me.

1059
01:28:26,635 --> 01:28:28,928
You've been on my nerves a long time!

1060
01:28:50,825 --> 01:28:52,910
You always wanted to fly, Kent.

1061
01:28:53,119 --> 01:28:54,328
Now's your chance.

1062
01:33:48,456 --> 01:33:49,957
Skipper!

1063
01:34:04,597 --> 01:34:06,974
God, would you look at that!

1064
01:34:54,397 --> 01:34:57,024
Miss Lorelei Ambrosia
isn't at home right now.

1065
01:34:57,233 --> 01:34:59,443
But if you'd care to leave a message...

1066
01:34:59,652 --> 01:35:03,030
why not deliver it to her in person?

1067
01:35:03,197 --> 01:35:06,575
So you've finally shown
your true colors.

1068
01:35:06,784 --> 01:35:11,038
Well, if you're looking for us,
here's where you'll find us.

1069
01:35:11,247 --> 01:35:12,956
Do drop in.

1070
01:35:19,547 --> 01:35:21,214
Wow, this is fun!

1071
01:35:21,633 --> 01:35:23,675
Fun? The fun's just starting.

1072
01:35:24,260 --> 01:35:27,095
Wait till Superman finds us,
then you'll see some fun.

1073
01:35:27,305 --> 01:35:29,681
Wait, you gonna mess with Superman?

1074
01:35:29,974 --> 01:35:33,977
Let's go. I want to be ready for him
when he falls into our trap.

1075
01:35:34,270 --> 01:35:38,106
I just don't see why you can't
balloon down like the rest of us.

1076
01:35:38,316 --> 01:35:39,399
Well...

1077
01:35:41,235 --> 01:35:42,361
No way.

1078
01:35:42,570 --> 01:35:45,072
I just don't believe a man can fly.

1079
01:36:02,256 --> 01:36:04,257
Watch out, horsy!

1080
01:36:13,976 --> 01:36:16,103
Don't, don't, don't.

1081
01:36:16,270 --> 01:36:18,689
Just don't try to fly.

1082
01:36:18,940 --> 01:36:20,399
Don't try to fly!

1083
01:36:33,621 --> 01:36:36,081
Will you get out of my way!

1084
01:36:54,892 --> 01:36:57,227
- Hurry! Hurry up!
- I am hurrying.

1085
01:37:02,817 --> 01:37:05,110
- I can't see anything.
- Turn on the light.

1086
01:37:05,278 --> 01:37:08,029
- Where's the light switch?
- Where do you usually find it?

1087
01:37:08,239 --> 01:37:10,532
I don't know.
I guess I'll check the doorway.

1088
01:37:10,742 --> 01:37:14,619
God, it's pitch-black in here.
Oh, that's better.

1089
01:37:18,082 --> 01:37:20,834
Wow, what a jukebox!

1090
01:37:21,002 --> 01:37:22,961
I told you, didn't I?

1091
01:37:23,129 --> 01:37:25,422
There. The ultimate computer!

1092
01:37:32,597 --> 01:37:36,349
It does everything a computer can do
and 1000 things none of them can do.

1093
01:37:36,559 --> 01:37:37,976
Let's give it a dry run.

1094
01:37:38,186 --> 01:37:40,103
Wait a minute.
We've gotta wait for Gus.

1095
01:37:40,313 --> 01:37:41,605
Who needs Gus?

1096
01:37:41,773 --> 01:37:45,150
- He's the only one who can operate it.
- Like fish he is!

1097
01:37:45,359 --> 01:37:48,570
I know enough about computers
to put a PhD to shame.

1098
01:37:48,780 --> 01:37:51,323
Come now, brother dear,
you didn't think...

1099
01:37:51,491 --> 01:37:54,201
I was gonna let that little man
run the show, did you?

1100
01:37:54,577 --> 01:37:56,620
Why don't peons tidy up
when they're done?

1101
01:37:56,829 --> 01:37:59,623
Come on, Bubba, it's showtime.

1102
01:38:03,044 --> 01:38:05,712
Engage those buttons
to activate the alpha circuit...

1103
01:38:05,922 --> 01:38:07,297
and lock the modular grid.

1104
01:38:07,507 --> 01:38:12,385
You! Activate circuits 29 through W-7...

1105
01:38:12,595 --> 01:38:16,681
and start full-power coordinates
on exterior defensive systems.

1106
01:38:16,891 --> 01:38:19,768
In other words, push this red button.

1107
01:38:20,603 --> 01:38:22,604
How did you know about that?

1108
01:38:40,540 --> 01:38:41,581
He's here!

1109
01:38:41,749 --> 01:38:44,751
Good. Let's give him
something to worry about.

1110
01:38:45,837 --> 01:38:47,295
Now, let's see...

1111
01:38:47,755 --> 01:38:50,131
Tracking systems locked.

1112
01:39:15,616 --> 01:39:17,617
Let the games begin.

1113
01:39:18,619 --> 01:39:20,245
Don't tense up now, honey.

1114
01:39:52,778 --> 01:39:55,655
Come on, Bubba,
you're wasting your rockets.

1115
01:40:03,080 --> 01:40:05,165
Come on, Superman!

1116
01:40:06,250 --> 01:40:08,126
Let him have it, Ross.

1117
01:40:15,009 --> 01:40:16,843
Bubba, keep firing.

1118
01:40:17,011 --> 01:40:19,679
Keep him occupied
while I get the MX ready.

1119
01:40:46,916 --> 01:40:49,125
What the hell is going on?

1120
01:40:57,218 --> 01:41:00,887
You keep your rockets coming.
He won't notice the missile till too late!

1121
01:41:09,063 --> 01:41:11,231
So much for your catlike reflexes.

1122
01:41:21,701 --> 01:41:23,284
Oh, God!

1123
01:41:24,620 --> 01:41:26,162
Ha, ha!

1124
01:41:33,254 --> 01:41:36,214
No more. Look, you sit.

1125
01:41:36,424 --> 01:41:38,216
Sit, sit!

1126
01:41:41,929 --> 01:41:43,054
Help!

1127
01:41:43,764 --> 01:41:46,933
Hello? Forget you, jackass!

1128
01:41:48,185 --> 01:41:49,519
That's him out of the way.

1129
01:41:49,687 --> 01:41:53,773
Sis, how would you like to control
all the world's weapons systems?

1130
01:41:54,650 --> 01:41:55,859
Baby!

1131
01:41:56,068 --> 01:41:57,527
It's Daddy!

1132
01:41:58,612 --> 01:42:00,780
Hey, what are you doing with my baby?

1133
01:42:01,240 --> 01:42:05,410
Gus, old buddy, genius.
Come up and join the fun.

1134
01:42:16,297 --> 01:42:19,883
He's still coming.
Arm the inner defenses.

1135
01:42:24,305 --> 01:42:25,805
All right, the game's over.

1136
01:42:26,474 --> 01:42:27,515
Hi, honey.

1137
01:42:28,059 --> 01:42:29,225
I don't know you, lady.

1138
01:42:31,270 --> 01:42:32,479
But the other night...

1139
01:42:35,107 --> 01:42:37,317
I'm sorry, but that wasn't me.

1140
01:42:37,485 --> 01:42:38,818
That guy's gone.

1141
01:42:40,613 --> 01:42:42,072
And you're next, Webster.

1142
01:42:43,199 --> 01:42:46,618
Never underestimate
the power of computers.

1143
01:42:46,911 --> 01:42:48,244
How do you like it?

1144
01:42:48,454 --> 01:42:50,997
I think it's typical
of people like you, Webster.

1145
01:42:51,290 --> 01:42:54,667
Instead of helping others, the four
of you just wanna help yourselves.

1146
01:42:54,835 --> 01:42:57,170
Four of you?

1147
01:42:57,338 --> 01:42:59,464
You mean, us? Four? Wait...

1148
01:42:59,673 --> 01:43:01,341
Hey, man!

1149
01:43:01,509 --> 01:43:05,178
That's only his last name.
He likes to be called "Superman".

1150
01:43:05,971 --> 01:43:08,598
See, I'm not with them, Superman.

1151
01:43:09,183 --> 01:43:10,600
You could've fooled me, mister.

1152
01:43:18,943 --> 01:43:20,443
That's very good.

1153
01:43:22,905 --> 01:43:26,407
Let's see how long
he can carry on without any air.

1154
01:43:48,556 --> 01:43:50,515
He's still coming!
He's going to get me!

1155
01:43:50,683 --> 01:43:51,808
Don't bet on it!

1156
01:44:04,488 --> 01:44:05,864
You're hurting him.

1157
01:44:09,952 --> 01:44:12,036
- That's Kryptonite!
- Yes.

1158
01:44:12,204 --> 01:44:14,747
- This time we got it right!
- You're a genius.

1159
01:44:15,291 --> 01:44:18,877
You've invented a machine
that can find anybody's weak spot.

1160
01:44:19,378 --> 01:44:20,920
Congratulations, old buddy.

1161
01:44:21,088 --> 01:44:24,340
You'll go down in history
as the man who killed Superman!

1162
01:44:24,550 --> 01:44:25,758
I'm... No.

1163
01:44:26,468 --> 01:44:27,760
Superman!

1164
01:44:27,928 --> 01:44:29,512
No!

1165
01:44:30,055 --> 01:44:32,348
- Where do you think you're going?
- Never mind.

1166
01:44:32,516 --> 01:44:35,435
- Turn the power up.
- Hasn't he had enough?

1167
01:44:39,273 --> 01:44:40,565
Turn it up!

1168
01:44:40,733 --> 01:44:42,859
Power! More power!

1169
01:44:47,323 --> 01:44:49,199
Whoa!

1170
01:44:54,246 --> 01:44:55,538
Ow!

1171
01:45:04,298 --> 01:45:06,966
Seventy-five. Current 7.75.

1172
01:45:11,055 --> 01:45:15,808
There's a current level of 7
that is not supposed to be on bar...

1173
01:45:16,018 --> 01:45:17,602
Oh, here it is!

1174
01:45:44,255 --> 01:45:45,296
What's going on?

1175
01:45:46,173 --> 01:45:48,007
I don't know. The power's gone.

1176
01:45:48,467 --> 01:45:50,343
Gus must have pulled the plug out.

1177
01:45:50,844 --> 01:45:52,303
It worked.

1178
01:45:52,513 --> 01:45:54,847
It worked! I got it!

1179
01:45:58,852 --> 01:46:00,353
What have you got?

1180
01:46:02,856 --> 01:46:04,607
- Give me that screw.
- This screw?

1181
01:46:04,817 --> 01:46:06,943
- That screw.
- Never!

1182
01:46:11,365 --> 01:46:13,866
Hey, wait. I can't see.

1183
01:46:36,432 --> 01:46:37,557
What?

1184
01:46:40,394 --> 01:46:41,853
Holy!

1185
01:46:42,396 --> 01:46:44,564
No! Make it stop!

1186
01:46:46,191 --> 01:46:47,650
I can't! It's out of control!

1187
01:46:47,860 --> 01:46:51,029
But how? Where's it getting
the power from?

1188
01:46:54,575 --> 01:46:56,784
It's feeding itself.

1189
01:46:56,994 --> 01:46:58,244
It wants to live!

1190
01:47:21,143 --> 01:47:23,311
It's this thing here. We'll go to the zoo.

1191
01:47:23,520 --> 01:47:26,773
I'll do that tomorrow,
and then we'll go on to the...

1192
01:47:27,900 --> 01:47:30,443
- What's happening?
- It's okay, Ricky.

1193
01:47:30,694 --> 01:47:31,861
Put the lights on!

1194
01:47:51,799 --> 01:47:53,841
Stop it! You're killing him!

1195
01:47:55,636 --> 01:47:57,011
Stop it!

1196
01:48:09,483 --> 01:48:10,900
Hey. Put me down!

1197
01:48:28,168 --> 01:48:31,254
Don't leave us alone in here! Superman!

1198
01:48:35,592 --> 01:48:36,717
Oh, I get it.

1199
01:48:36,885 --> 01:48:40,471
The coaxial energy shaft is engaging
the grid source factor. Right.

1200
01:48:40,681 --> 01:48:42,515
We're through, frogface.
I'm splitting.

1201
01:48:42,683 --> 01:48:44,267
Hey, wait a minute!

1202
01:48:46,812 --> 01:48:49,480
Girls. Girls, come out of there!

1203
01:48:59,116 --> 01:49:01,367
Help me! Please!

1204
01:49:08,041 --> 01:49:09,167
Sis?

1205
01:49:13,005 --> 01:49:14,297
Oh, my God.

1206
01:49:21,889 --> 01:49:23,181
What is that?

1207
01:49:34,776 --> 01:49:36,027
Lorelei!

1208
01:49:38,572 --> 01:49:40,740
Sis, it's your Bubba!

1209
01:50:18,779 --> 01:50:20,446
Help me. Help!

1210
01:50:22,658 --> 01:50:23,950
Superman!

1211
01:50:27,037 --> 01:50:28,120
Honey!

1212
01:50:28,288 --> 01:50:32,166
Honey, I'm stuck here! Help!
What about me?

1213
01:50:43,303 --> 01:50:44,345
Look out!

1214
01:52:53,684 --> 01:52:54,892
Bubba?

1215
01:53:41,231 --> 01:53:42,982
Thank you, brother.

1216
01:53:49,990 --> 01:53:51,699
Regular or premium?

1217
01:53:51,908 --> 01:53:55,995
She hasn't had a drink in so long,
give her a tankful of the good stuff.

1218
01:53:57,914 --> 01:53:58,956
How you doing?

1219
01:53:59,124 --> 01:54:02,209
Please don't talk to me.
I'm having enough trouble hanging on.

1220
01:54:02,419 --> 01:54:05,171
Okay, we'll go slow.
You're perfectly safe.

1221
01:54:05,797 --> 01:54:07,214
I'm not gonna argue with you.

1222
01:54:07,382 --> 01:54:10,509
I mean, any man who can trick
my machine can do anything.

1223
01:54:10,677 --> 01:54:12,386
How did you beat my defenses?

1224
01:54:12,596 --> 01:54:16,015
Those defenses are good as long
as it didn't know it's in trouble.

1225
01:54:16,224 --> 01:54:19,727
This time it didn't see the danger.
I went in with plain old acid.

1226
01:54:19,936 --> 01:54:23,564
It didn't know that when acid gets hot,
it'll eat through anything.

1227
01:54:24,107 --> 01:54:25,691
- Watch the trees.
- Whoa!

1228
01:54:26,276 --> 01:54:29,361
I guess it died of acid indigestion.

1229
01:54:30,614 --> 01:54:33,199
But what's gonna happen
to Ross and the ladies?

1230
01:54:33,366 --> 01:54:36,911
They're gonna have to see the police.
It's not your problem anymore.

1231
01:54:38,455 --> 01:54:39,997
Are we in Metropolis yet?

1232
01:54:40,207 --> 01:54:43,292
Nope. We're just gonna make
a little stop right over there.

1233
01:54:43,502 --> 01:54:45,419
Whoa!

1234
01:54:50,967 --> 01:54:53,511
We're on the ground, Gus.
Morning.

1235
01:54:53,678 --> 01:54:55,679
- You okay, Supe?
- I'm fine.

1236
01:54:55,889 --> 01:54:57,056
Excuse me a second.

1237
01:55:01,394 --> 01:55:03,187
Can you guys spare one of these?

1238
01:55:04,064 --> 01:55:06,774
- Sure, Superman.
- It is Superman, isn't it?

1239
01:55:06,983 --> 01:55:08,984
Are you kidding? Is that?

1240
01:55:09,194 --> 01:55:11,904
Didn't you see us fly out of the sky?

1241
01:55:13,114 --> 01:55:17,701
We're the only two men who can fly.
"Is it Superman?"

1242
01:55:17,911 --> 01:55:19,411
Just right.

1243
01:55:20,247 --> 01:55:21,288
Okay, Gus, let's go.

1244
01:55:21,498 --> 01:55:24,583
I was afraid you'd say that.
I thought I'd take the bus.

1245
01:55:25,085 --> 01:55:28,420
Well, suit yourself.
Does your boss have a computer here?

1246
01:55:28,755 --> 01:55:31,674
Yeah, he got a little bitty one
about that big.

1247
01:55:31,842 --> 01:55:35,511
You tell him he can do a lot worse
than to give Gus Gorman here a job.

1248
01:55:37,764 --> 01:55:39,348
Wow, thank you, Supe.

1249
01:55:39,683 --> 01:55:40,724
Take care.

1250
01:55:42,602 --> 01:55:44,103
I'll see you around.

1251
01:55:50,193 --> 01:55:51,277
So long.

1252
01:55:54,322 --> 01:55:56,031
Take it easy, man.

1253
01:55:57,409 --> 01:56:01,620
Well, you got good references,
so if you want that job...

1254
01:56:05,667 --> 01:56:08,460
Nah, this is not for me.
I think I'll take that bus.

1255
01:56:08,628 --> 01:56:10,546
Can you tell me
where the bus station is?

1256
01:56:10,755 --> 01:56:13,340
Yeah, about nine, 10 miles over there.

1257
01:56:13,550 --> 01:56:18,012
Nine or 10 miles. Okay.

1258
01:56:18,179 --> 01:56:20,264
Hey. You really flew with him?

1259
01:56:20,432 --> 01:56:23,475
Superman? Have you ever
seen Superman before?

1260
01:56:25,478 --> 01:56:26,520
No.

1261
01:56:26,813 --> 01:56:30,316
Oh, you don't know about me and him?
Me and Superman?

1262
01:56:35,488 --> 01:56:37,823
Yeah, we go way back together.

1263
01:56:37,991 --> 01:56:40,659
We always, usually, sometimes, we...

1264
01:56:42,120 --> 01:56:43,871
Nine or 10 miles?

1265
01:56:44,414 --> 01:56:46,332
I think I'll walk.

1266
01:56:46,708 --> 01:56:48,125
Yeah, I'll walk.

1267
01:56:48,710 --> 01:56:49,919
Yeah.

1268
01:56:54,966 --> 01:56:56,175
Clark.

1269
01:56:56,509 --> 01:56:59,511
What a nice surprise! Come in.

1270
01:56:59,679 --> 01:57:01,263
- Gosh. Hi, Mr. Kent.
- Hi, Ricky.

1271
01:57:01,431 --> 01:57:03,933
- Guess who Mom's having dinner with.
- Who?

1272
01:57:04,142 --> 01:57:05,517
Superman!

1273
01:57:06,061 --> 01:57:08,270
Yeah, that's what I came to tell you.

1274
01:57:08,480 --> 01:57:10,356
Superman said to tell you he's sorry...

1275
01:57:10,565 --> 01:57:14,234
but he's run into a problem and he
won't be able to have dinner with you.

1276
01:57:14,402 --> 01:57:16,695
- I guess he misses a lot of dinners.
- Yeah.

1277
01:57:17,864 --> 01:57:19,740
Would you mind settling for me?

1278
01:57:19,950 --> 01:57:21,200
Any day.

1279
01:57:22,077 --> 01:57:23,410
- I'll get my things.
- Okay.

1280
01:57:25,330 --> 01:57:28,832
You know, Lana, I was talking
to Superman the other day.

1281
01:57:29,042 --> 01:57:32,795
You know, he and I, we talk a lot.

1282
01:57:33,296 --> 01:57:36,632
And he felt badly about you having
to pawn your diamond ring.

1283
01:57:39,719 --> 01:57:41,220
Well, he found...

1284
01:57:42,430 --> 01:57:45,641
He found this one just lying around.

1285
01:57:46,935 --> 01:57:49,395
He wanted you to have this.

1286
01:57:56,236 --> 01:57:58,195
Wow, a ring from Superman!

1287
01:57:59,364 --> 01:58:01,156
- It's okay. I got it.
- Sorry.

1288
01:58:01,324 --> 01:58:02,741
Look at that.

1289
01:58:03,576 --> 01:58:05,911
- Oh, Clark.
- It's okay.

1290
01:58:06,121 --> 01:58:07,413
It fits.

1291
01:58:07,914 --> 01:58:09,248
It looks really pretty.

1292
01:58:09,416 --> 01:58:10,791
Thank you.

1293
01:58:11,835 --> 01:58:13,502
Well...

1294
01:58:13,670 --> 01:58:14,753
- Brad.
- Brad.

1295
01:58:15,213 --> 01:58:16,255
Son of a bitch.

1296
01:58:18,091 --> 01:58:20,009
Kent, I hate you.

1297
01:58:20,927 --> 01:58:22,845
I've always hated you.

1298
01:58:23,388 --> 01:58:25,139
- You know why?
- No.

1299
01:58:25,306 --> 01:58:26,932
- Because you're nice.
- Not really.

1300
01:58:27,142 --> 01:58:28,600
And nice guys finish last.

1301
01:58:40,405 --> 01:58:42,031
Lois, I've got to hand it to you.

1302
01:58:42,240 --> 01:58:44,616
Who else could turn
a vacation into a story...

1303
01:58:44,826 --> 01:58:47,786
that'll blow the lid off
of corruption in the Caribbean?

1304
01:58:47,996 --> 01:58:51,290
I knew I was on to something
when that taxi driver kidnapped me.

1305
01:58:51,499 --> 01:58:53,500
Lois, you're terrific.

1306
01:58:53,710 --> 01:58:57,087
I have to be. Seems I've got
some new competition.

1307
01:58:57,297 --> 01:58:58,672
Hmm?

1308
01:58:59,007 --> 01:59:01,550
The story that you wrote
on the class reunion?

1309
01:59:01,760 --> 01:59:03,552
- I thought it was terrific.
- Thanks.

1310
01:59:03,720 --> 01:59:07,347
And fascinating. I liked the part
about the little girl back home.

1311
01:59:07,515 --> 01:59:09,808
I'll take you to lunch
and you tell me about it.

1312
01:59:10,643 --> 01:59:13,937
I'd love to, but I'm having lunch
with Mr. White's new secretary.

1313
01:59:14,105 --> 01:59:15,147
- Hi, Lana.
- Hi, Clark.

1314
01:59:15,315 --> 01:59:19,651
Lana. Lois, say hello to Lana Lang,
Smallville's newest gift to Metropolis.

1315
01:59:19,819 --> 01:59:22,279
I'm glad to meet you.
I like your writing a lot.

1316
01:59:22,655 --> 01:59:23,739
Thank you.

1317
01:59:24,699 --> 01:59:26,033
I like your sparkler a lot.

1318
01:59:26,242 --> 01:59:29,161
Me too. I couldn't believe it
when Clark gave it to me.

1319
01:59:30,663 --> 01:59:32,790
- Clark gave it to you?
- Yes.

1320
01:59:35,502 --> 01:59:36,877
Mr. White.

1321
01:59:37,087 --> 01:59:40,214
Mr. White, look what I've got for you.

1322
01:59:40,423 --> 01:59:43,342
People, I am in love with this machine!

1323
01:59:43,510 --> 01:59:48,138
Mr. White, excuse me, but I have
a couple of errands to run before lunch.

1324
01:59:48,348 --> 01:59:51,058
- Go ahead, Mr. White.
- Where's the handle?

1325
01:59:51,267 --> 01:59:54,520
There is no handle.
You just push the button.

